4. Notification of Derivative Works: Any creation of derivative works or Torollama Materials from "Torollama" must be promptly notified to Taureau AI at (contact@taureau.ai).

5. Compliance with Laws and Regulations: All distributions of "Torollama" or its derivative works or Torollama Materials must comply with the applicable laws and regulations.

6. Copyright and Documentation Integrity: All distributions of "Torollama" or its derivative works or Torollama Materials must retain all original copyright and documentation information of both "Torollama" and "LLAMA 2".

7. Restrictions on Competitive Usage: "Torollama" or its derivative works or Torollama Materials shall not be used to develop products or services that directly compete with the Torus ecosystem, unless a specific agreement is in place with AllbyAI.

8. Prohibition on Improving Other Language Models: "Torollama" or its derivative works or Torollama Materials shall not be used to improve other language models, except for "Torollama" and its derivative works or Torollama Materials.

9. Additional Commercial Terms: If the number of active users per month of the products or services utilizing "Torollama" or its derivative works or Torollama Materials exceeds 1 million, an additional license must be requested from AllbyAI. For over 700 million active users, an additional license from Meta is required.

10. Termination Clause: This Agreement may be terminated by AllbyAI upon any breach of these terms and conditions or the core terms of the "LLAMA 2 Community License Agreement".

By agreeing to this License, you acknowledge and agree to adhere to both the core principles of the "LLAMA 2 Community License Agreement" and the supplementary terms and conditions specified herein for the use of "Torollama".
